<mixertitle>GAP package HAPcryst</mixertitle>

<h2>A HAP extension for crytallographic groups</h2>
<p class="homelink">[<a href="http://csserver.evansville.edu/~mroeder/HAPcryst.html">WWW homepage</a>]</p>
<h4>Author</h4>
<p><a href="http://csserver.evansville.edu/~mroeder">Marc Roeder</a></p>
<h4>Short Description</h4>
<p><![CDATA[This is an extension to the HAP package by Graham Ellis. It implements geometric methods for the calculation of resolutions of Bieberbach groups.]]>
</p>

<mixer part="extra" needed="no"/>

<h4>Version</h4>
<p> Current version number 0.1.11 &nbsp;&nbsp;(Released  27/10/2013)
</p>
<h4>Status</h4>
<p>deposited
</p>
<h4>Dependencies</h4>
<p>
<span class='pkgname'>GAP</span> version: >=4.4.10<br />Needed other packages: Polycyclic(>=2.8.1), AClib(>=1.1), cryst(>=4.1.5), HAP(>=1.8), polymaking(>=0.7.9), <br />Suggested other packages: Carat(>=1.1), CrystCat(>=1.1.2), GAPDoc(>= 0.99), <br />External needs: polymake (http://www.polymake.org) must be installed to calculate resolutions
</p>
